args: I really wanted to spend it with Garuda...
*gasp* Was that...?! No. Just the wind.
Ack, and RAIN! This is becoming the\nworst Halloween ever...
Lowen, hurry inside! You'll catch cold!
With the weather as it is, we'll have\nto call off the party.
It might stop! And Garuda might still\nmake it back in time.
I know how you feel, Lowen, but this isn't\nthe kind of storm that passes in a blink.
And even if it did, the ground would be\nall wet and muddy—hardly conditions\nfor a party.
What in the... The clouds are being blown\naway! And the ground is drying up!
Forgive me, Lowen. I am quite late.
What is it? You look as if you've seen\na ghost.
And why wouldn't we?! Do you have any\nidea what TIME it is?!
Pray forgive my tardiness.\nIn truth, I was a bit...lost.
You mean you just got turned around?
Not quite. Rather, I could not decide what\nmanner of treat Lowen would like best.
It is customary for Halloween participants\nto share treats with one another, yes?
I have always been the recipient of gifts;\nit has been a long time indeed since I\nwas the giver.
And so I worried a great deal, flying this\nway and that, ultimately delaying my\nreturn until this moment.
I am very sorry to have caused you undue\nworry, Lowen. Pray forgive me for—
S-sorry! And, um...sorry for everything\nelse, too.
Nonsense. You have nothing to apologize\nfor. I kept you waiting, after all.
But you were thinking about me the\nwhole time...
And I was just being selfish. I just\nkept thinking how I wanted to see you,\nand those feelings met you on the wind.
He told me the same thing, Garuda.\nLowen believes he's been a very bad boy.
He says he upset you by thinking only of\nwhat he wanted, and not what you did.
Poppycock. I was delighted to know how\nbadly you missed me!
That's why I was so intent to find the\nperfect treat for you. In the end, though,\nI only succeeded in causing you distress.
That's enough apologizing from you.\nIn fact, I would prefer you be even\nMORE selfish.
Not in the slightest. You deny yourself\ntoo much, Lowen.
Agreed! You have to speak up when\nyou want something.

It's okay to be selfish sometimes—it
doesn't always mean you're bothering
someone! If you stay quiet, how will
anyone know your true feelings?
Moreover, today is Halloween. Is this not\na day for children to enjoy themselves?
Are you saying it's okay for me to be\nselfish and play pranks and stuff?
Yes. To make up for my tardiness,\nI shall weather all you can muster.
Hee hee! All right then... Trick or treat!
If you want me to let go, you better give\nme a treat! Hee hee!
Easy, Lowen! Not every dragon\nis a hugger.
Garuda, maybe you had better\ngive him his treat.
Phew. I was...not prepared for\nsuch a reaction.
What did she bring you, Lowen?
It's a bunch of candy shaped like feathers,\nin really pretty colors! I love it!
Honestly, I'd be happy with anything if\nit came from you.
Garuda? Your face is all red,\nwhat's wrong?
A-anyway, Lowen, it looks like you\nmanaged to prank Garuda after all.\nHow did you pull that off?
I thought you said pranking people\nwasn't really your thing.
Well, I still don't like doing pranks that\ncause people trouble.
But Garuda said it was okay, and I figured\nit would make our Halloween together\nmore fun...
So maybe being a prankster is okay\nsometimes!
I did say you could play a prank, but...\nPerhaps you shouldn't make a habit\nof hugging people so suddenly.
W-was it too much? Oh no, I'm sorry!
Even my nice pranks end up failing...
It's not that I didn't like it. I just... Well,\nI suppose I was a bit troubled by how\nhappy it made me.
Louise! Some assistance, please.\nI yet struggle with matters of\nthe heart.
What do you expect ME to do?!
Your heart?!\nGaruda, does your heart hurt?!
No, that's not what I mean!
H-hey Lowen, why don't we all go enjoy\nwhat's left of the party?
Garuda blew the clouds away, after all.
Y-yes! A terrific idea. Shall we?
Well all right, but...are you sure\nyou're okay?
Of course. Now, let us begin our tricking\nand treating!
Yeah! Do you know what you say after?
